4e4c60e8-acfa-44ce-8d81-8792c5392f6d.584cdae4-3b00-4872-8108-07e5600f282a.description=
Counts from one number to another number.

Inputs\:
from - The number to start counting at
to - The number to count to
incrementBy - The amount to increment by during each count.
reset - If set to true, then the counter will restart counting from the beginning.

Responses\:
has more - Not yet done counting.
failure - Something went wrong.
no more - Done counting. This will only be returned once, then counting restarts.

Returns\:
The number that was just counted.
4e4c60e8-acfa-44ce-8d81-8792c5392f6d.8642b256-105a-473c-97fb-07a1f64b7eba.description=Reboot the given Server managed in SA. Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to Connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. agent - Name of the server to reboot now. wait - An integer value specifying How many milliseconds should be waited for the job to finish. If not specified the job is started, but may not have finished. Responses\: success - The operation completed successfully. failure - Something went wrong. Returns\: returnResult - The id of the job created. 4e4c60e8-acfa-44ce-8d81-8792c5392f6d.97c0044a-d7d1-4656-97ca-1321cda34b30.description=
This operation loops as many times as specified in the "count" input, counting from "1" to a greater number, incrementing it by "1" at each iteration.

Inputs\:
    count - The number of loops to complete.
Valid values\: from 1 to 9223372036854775807
    reset - Specifies whether the counter restarts counting from "1".
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: false
    to - The number to count to. It will take the value of the "count" input field. 
    from - The number to start counting at. For this operation, it is customized to "1".
    incrementBy - The number to increment by while counting. For this operation, it is customized to "1".

Results\:
    resultString – This is the primary output. It contains the value of the number that was just counted.

Responses\:
    has more – The counting process is not complete. One or more iterations are pending.
    no more – The counting process is complete.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

Note\:
1. It is recommended that you do not change the values of the "to", "from" or "incrementBy" input fields.
2. The "from", "to" and "incrementBy" inputs are customized for this operation. Even though you can also customize them, if you need to specify the loop range borders and the increment value, use the "Counter" operation.

Examples\:
1. For a loop with 20 iterations, the following values should be provided for the input fields\:
    count\: 20
    reset\: false (this field can also be left blank, as "false" is the default value)
2. For an infinite loop, the value of "count" should be at least "1" and the value of "reset" should be "true".
4e4c60e8-acfa-44ce-8d81-8792c5392f6d.b8d883e7-0532-49f2-b24c-5b5fd5352371.description=

Responses\:

Returns\:
The number that was just counted.

Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to Connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. attachedToType - The type of the objectto which the Custom Attribute is attached to (must be one of [SERVERS, DEVICE_GROUPS, SOFTWARE_POLICIES, CUSTOMERS]. attachedToName - The name of the object to which the Custom Attribute is attached to (e.g. name of server or device group, short name of customer etc). attachedToID - The id of the object to which the Custom Attribute is attached to (e.g. id of server or device group etc). Use this input for unique identification. name - The name of the attribute. value - The value of the attribute. Responses\: success - retrieved successfully failure - failed to retrieve data 4e4c60e8-acfa-44ce-8d81-8792c5392f6d.da5289c8-144d-43b0-bce7-c03868e9e667.description=

    resultString – This is the primary output. It contains the "completed sleep" message if the operation completed successfully and an error message otherwise.
